# Syntax highlighting for .qedspec files on GitHub.
#
# F# is the closest existing highlighter for v2.8+ qedspec syntax:
#   - `//` line comments (qedspec uses these; OCaml's `(* … *)` form
#      visually breaks every comment line)
#   - `type T = | A | B of T` ADT variants
#   - `:` for type annotations, `->` for arrows
#   - `if … then … else …` (v2.8 F9 fold-in)
#
# Pairs with the in-doc fence migration (` ```fsharp `) so the GitHub
# diff viewer, blob viewer, and inline-doc renderer all agree.
*.qedspec linguist-language=F#
*.qedspec linguist-detectable=true
